'''Karly Gaitán Morales''' ([[Managua]], [[Nicaragua]], March 25, 1980) is a Nicaraguan writer, journalist, and [[film historian]].<ref>{{cite news|title=One Hundred Personalities of Nicaraguan Cinema: Rossana Lacayo|url=http://www.caratula.net/ediciones/59/cine-kgaitan.php|work= Carátula Magazine|accessdate= 2014-04-29}}</ref>

==Early years and education==
She was born and raised in [[Managua]], Nicaragua. She graduated from the [[Central American University (Managua)|Universidad Centroamericana (UCA) in Managua]], Faculty of Communication. She obtained a diploma in Social Communication and Written Press.<ref>{{cite news|title=Biography: Karly Gaitán Morales|url=http://www.escritorasnicaragua.org/biografias/karlygaitan|work=ANIDE|accessdate=2014-04-28}}</ref>

== Literary work ==
She is a contributor for ''La Prensa Literaria'',<ref>{{cite news|title=Cinema Law in Nicaragua, Why?|url=http://www.laprensa.com.ni/2010/10/16/suplemento/la-prensa-literaria/3039|work=La Prensa Literaria|accessdate=2014-04-29}}</ref> the ''Nuevo Amanecer Cultural''<ref>{{cite news|title=Frida Kahlo...Pata de Palo!|url=http://impreso.elnuevodiario.com.ni/2007/11/24/suplemento/nuevoamanecer/7400|work=Nuevo Amanecer Cultural (Nicaragua)|accessdate=2014-04-29}}</ref> and ''Voces de La Prensa''.<ref>{{cite news|title=Sergio Ramírez 50 years of Literary Work|url=http://www.laprensa.com.ni/2012/06/30/voces/106795-sergio-ramirez-50-anos|work=La Prensa (Nicaragua)|accessdate=2014-04-29}}</ref> She is a member of the Nicaraguan Association of Women Writers, in Spanish, ''Asociación Nicaragüense de Escritoras'' (ANIDE). She is a board member of the Foundation for Cinematography and Images, in Spanish, ''Fundación para la Cinematografía y la imagen'' (FUCINE).

In 2012, she published her first book titled ''An interview with Sergio Ramírez. Interviews. Articles. Chronicles'', original title in Spanish ''Cita con Sergio Ramírez. Entrevistas. Artículos. Crónicas'',<ref>{{cite news|title=Critic: An Interview with Sergio Ramírez by Karly Gaitán|url= http://www.caratula.net/ediciones/55/critica-eaguirre.php|work=Carátula Magazine (Managua)|accessdate=2014-04-29}}</ref> first edition 2012 [[Universidad Autónoma de Nuevo León]], [[Monterrey]], [[Mexico]], about the Nicaraguan writer [[Sergio Ramírez]] in commemoration of his 50th anniversary as a writer.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.elnuevodiario.com.ni/suplemento/nuevoamanecer/3068-cita-sergio-ramirez-o-acompanando-al-escritor|title=An Interview with Sergio Ramírez or in the Writer's Company|last=Llana|first=Carlos|date=December 6, 2007|work=Nuevo Amanecer Cultural (Nicaragua)|accessdate=2014-04-29|first2=}}</ref> The prologue for this book was written by the Nicaraguan writer Luis Rocha Urtecho. This book was officially presented<ref>{{cite news|title=Nicaraguan Journalist Presents her Book|url=http://noticias.lainformacion.com/arte-cultura-y-espectaculos/literatura/periodista-nicaraguense-presenta-su-libro-cita-con-sergio-ramirez-mercado_DVnIxnqqLeBdlURZYMUps7/|work= Agencia EFE|accessdate=2014-04-28}}</ref> at the [[Feria Internacional del Libro de Guadalajara]], Feria Internacional del Libro del Palacio de Minería in Mexico City, Feria Internacional del Libro de París (Salon du livre de Paris), and the [[Miami Book Fair International]]. The second edition has a prologue by the Costa Rican writer Carlos Cortés.

Gaitán Morales has compiled the history of cinematography in Nicaragua<ref>{{cite news|title=Moving Images of Rubén Darío|url=http://www.caratula.net/ediciones/50/cine-kgaitan.php|work=Carátula Magazine (Managua)|accessdate=2014-04-29}}</ref> into a book titled ''To Conquer a Dream. The History of Cinema in Nicaragua'', original title in Spanish, ''A la conquista de un sueño. Historia del cine en Nicaragua'',<ref>{{cite news|title=FUCINE Publications|url=http://www.fucine.org.ni/FUCINE___PROYECTOS.html|work=FUCINE Official Web Site|accessdate=2014-04-30|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140426214708/http://www.fucine.org.ni/FUCINE___PROYECTOS.html|archivedate=April 26, 2014|df=mdy-all}}</ref> with a presentation on the back cover by the Chilean writer [[Antonio Skármeta]]. This book covers the history of Nicaraguan films starting from the late 1800s to the present and it has been dubbed, by writer Rafael Lara, as the first "biography" of Nicaraguan cinema.<ref>{{cite news|title=The First National Biography of Cinema|url=http://www.elnuevodiario.com.ni/imprimir.php/97574 |work=El Nuevo Diario (Nicaragua)|accessdate=2014-04-30}}</ref>

==Published work==
*''Cita con Sergio Ramírez. Entrevistas. Artículos. Crónicas.'' (2012) Universidad Autónoma de Nuevo León, Monterrey, México
*''A la conquista de un sueño. Historia del cine en Nicaragua'' (2014) Managua, Nicaragua

